    <div class="container">
    
      <!-- Main Content Row -->
      <div class="main row">
        <div class="span8">
          <h1>Neo4j</h1>
          <p class="lead">Neo4j is the world's leading graph database.</p>
          <p>A graph database stores data in nodes and relationships with properties on both, something we call a <a href="/learn/propertygraph">Property Graph</a>. 
          Nodes are simply data records. Relationships are the connections between records.</p>
          <p>Neo4j is both an open source project, and a commercial product.  in a GPLv3 Community edition, with Advanced and Enterprise editions available under both the AGPLv3 and commercial licenses, supported by Neo Technology.</p>

 
          
          <div class="tabbable tabs-left">
            <h2>Neo4j Editions</h2>
            <ul class="nav nav-tabs">
              <li class="active"><a href="#community" data-toggle="tab">Community</a></li>
              <li><a href="#advanced" data-toggle="tab">Advanced</a></li>
              <li><a href="#enterprise" data-toggle="tab">Enterprise</a></li>
            </ul>
            <div class="tab-content">            
              <div class="tab-pane active" id="community">
                <table class="table table-striped">
                  <thead>
                    <tr><td>Features</td></tr>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody>
                    <tr><td>scalable - 32 Billion Nodes, 32 Billion Relationships, 64 Billion Properties</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>accessible - REST API with the usual language drivers</td></tr>
                    <tr><td>embeddable - use directly from any JVM-friendly language</td></tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
              </div>
              <div class="tab-pane" id="advanced">
                <table class="table table-striped">
                  <thead>
